as early as the 12th century, and became firmly established at the time of the Reformation, although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Nicholas de Prideaux was born in 1123, in Fowey, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Nicholas de Prideaux."},"et":{"1123–":"1123–Surnud","1130–1169":"1130–1169","1158–1225":"1158–1225","1160–1225":"1160–1225","1123–Female":"1123–Surnud","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1169":"1169","1123":"1123","about 1158":"umbes 1158","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Prideaux Castle, Fowey, Cornwall, England":"Fowey, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fowey, Cornwall, England":"Fowey, Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1123–":"1123–Kuollut","1130–1169":"1130–1169","1158–1225":"1158–1225","1160–1225":"1160–1225","1123–Female":"1123–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1169":"1169","1123":"1123","about 1158":"noin 1158","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Prideaux Castle, Fowey, Cornwall, England":"Fowey, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fowey, Cornwall, England":"Fowey, Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1123–":"1123–Décédée","1130–1169":"11